entries.title: EU Agrees to Expand Sanctions on Russian Oil Industry
entries.description: The bloc agreed to cap sales of premium products such as diesel at $100 a barrel and limit low-value ones such as fuel oil to $45 a barrel.

entries.title: Canada Pulls Back Proposed Rifle Ban From Gun-Control Measures
entries.description: Opposition from allies, farmers and indigenous communities prompts change to the marquee legislation.

entries.title: U.S. Presses Libyan Commander to Expel Russia's Wagner
entries.description: The CIA director visited Libya amid concerns the Kremlin-linked outfit, which has played an increasing battlefield role in the Ukraine war, may tap into the country’s oil riches.

entries.title: Russia's Ukraine War Effort Fueled by Turkish Exports
entries.description: Turkish companies last year exported tens of millions of dollars worth of machinery, electronics, spare parts and other items that Russia needs for its military, according to a survey of trade data.

entries.title: Blinken Trip to China Postponed After Alleged Spy Balloon Spotted Over U.S.
entries.description: The Biden administration has indefinitely postponed Secretary of State Antony Blinken’s trip to Beijing after determining that U.S. sovereignty was violated by what it identified as a Chinese reconnaissance balloon loitering above the continental U.S.

entries.title: One Father's Desperate Plan to Rescue His Son From America
entries.description: The Saleban family left Minnesota for Somaliland, where disobeying parents is illegal and carries a maximum penalty of six months in prison. “I am going to show you that Africa is not like America.”

entries.title: Russian Forces Strengthen Positions as Ukraine Braces for New Offensive
entries.description: Ukrainian officials have warned Russia is preparing for a fresh offensive to coincide with the first anniversary of its full-scale invasion.

entries.title: Europe Cuts Addiction to Russian Energy, Yet Fuel Scramble Continues
entries.description: Europe’s dependence on Russian energy is drawing to a close, leaving the continent racing to squirrel away fuels and find alternative supplies.

entries.title: Ukraine Hopes New Bombs From U.S. Will Help It Push Back Russia
entries.description: Ukraine last summer stunned Russian troops with precision strikes from U.S.-supplied Himars mobile rocket launchers. Now an even more potent rocket system holds the potential to re-energize Kyiv’s troops.

entries.title: China Says It Is Looking Into Spy-Balloon Allegation by U.S.
entries.description: Beijing said it was gathering information and that issue should be handled calmly and carefully.

entries.title: Chinese Spy Balloon Tracked Over U.S. This Week
entries.description: The U.S. tracked what officials described as a Chinese reconnaissance balloon over the U.S. this week, in what would be an aggressive act of intelligence gathering over sensitive U.S. national security sites.
